import pymongo
import pandas as pd

pdf = None

with pymongo.MongoClient('mongodb://witlab_mongo:defacto8*JxTo#@localhost:27017/')\
        as conn:
    db = conn.get_database('nl_witlab')
    print('DB: nl_witlab, Collections:', db.list_collection_names())
    collection = db.get_collection('cas_simple')
    result = collection.find()
    result_list = list(map(lambda s: dict(s), result))  # 병렬처리하니까 빠름
    pdf = pd.DataFrame(result_list)

paragraphs.title: ☆def filter function & init prerequisite obj
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_utc2kst_str, udf_dt2d, udf_dt2t


def get_spdf2dict(spdf):
    srslist = spdf.collect()
    srsdict = {}
    for r in srslist:
        srsdict[r['date']] = {'rise': r['rise'],
                              'culmination': r['culmination'],
                              'set' : r['set']}
    return srsdict

def isinsrs(srsdict, datetime: str):
    date = datetime.split()[0]
    time = datetime.split()[1]
    
    d = srsdict[date]
    if d['rise'] <= time <= d['set']:
        return True
    else: 
        return False

# 1. make sun rise set dataset to spdf
spdf_srs = spark.read.format('jdbc').options(
               url='jdbc:mysql://localhost/nl_witlab',
               driver='com.mysql.jdbc.Driver',
               dbtable='kasi_sun_riseset', user='root', password='defacto8*jj'
           ).load().select('date', 'rise', 'culmination', 'set')

# 1-1. show srs data spdf
spdf_srs.sort(spdf_srs.date.desc()).show()

# 2. convert spdf to dict
srsdict = get_spdf2dict(spdf_srs)

paragraphs.title: ☆do Filter
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

cas_raw = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/simple_new.parquet')\
               .withColumn('datetime', udf_utc2kst_str('datetime'))

# do srs filter
cas = cas_raw.rdd.filter(lambda r: isinsrs(srsdict, r['datetime']))\
             .toDF().sort('datetime')
cas.show()

%pyspark

def showCorrMtx(pdf, figsize: tuple, cmap="YlGnBu"):
    import numpy as np
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    import seaborn as sns
    
    corr = pdf.corr()
    mask = np.zeros_like(corr)
    mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True
    ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
    ax = sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, mask=mask, cmap=cmap)
